---

<section class="pfp" aria-labelledby="pfp-heading">
  <div class="container pfp-inner">
    <div class="pfp-media" aria-hidden="true" data-reveal>
      <div class="pfp-image-placeholder">
        <span>Image to be supplied</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pfp-content" data-reveal>
      <p class="pfp-eyebrow">What actually is passive fire protection?</p>
      <h2 id="pfp-heading" class="pfp-heading">How Passive Fire Protection Works</h2>

      <div class="pfp-body">
        <p><strong>You&rsquo;ve probably heard the term but most people don&rsquo;t know exactly what it means until something goes wrong.</strong></p>
        <p>Active fire protection is your alarms and extinguishers, the things that respond when a fire breaks out.</p>
        <p>Passive fire protection is what&rsquo;s built into the structure of the building itself.</p>
        <p><em>Fire doors. Sealed service penetrations. Cavity barriers. Compartment walls.</em></p>
        <p>These things don&rsquo;t make a noise or flash a light. They just quietly stop a fire from spreading while people get out safely.</p>
        <p>
          As a building owner or manager, keeping all of it maintained and compliant is your legal responsibility.
          <strong class="pfp-accent">That&rsquo;s where we come in.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>

      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary pfp-cta">Find out what your building needs</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pfp {
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    padding-block: 4.5em;
  }

  .pfp-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 26.5em 1fr;
    gap: 4em;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .pfp-media {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .pfp-image-placeholder {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 424 / 562;
    background-color: #d9d9d9;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--color-grey-soft);
    font-size: 0.875em;
  }

  .pfp-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5em;
    max-width: 36em;
  }

  .pfp-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--fs-xl); /* 36px */
    color: var(--color-mustard);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .pfp-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 2.75em; /* 44px */
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .pfp-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1em;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--fs-md); /* 20px */
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
  }

  .pfp-body strong {
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .pfp-accent {
    color: var(--color-mustard);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .pfp-cta {
    margin-top: 1em;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }

  @media (max-width: 991px) {
    .pfp-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2em;
    }
    .pfp-image-placeholder {
      max-width: 26.5em;
    }
    .pfp-heading {
      font-size: 2.25em;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .pfp-eyebrow {
      font-size: 1.75em;
    }
    .pfp-heading {
      font-size: 1.875em;
    }
    .pfp-body {
      font-size: 1em;
    }
  }
</style>
